            "headline": "CA Surgeon General Dr. Diana Ramos launches PSA to raise awareness of Adverse Childhood Experiences & Toxic Stress.",
            "id": "ae750ed4-d746-47ba-ba93-6146fd6fc8fe",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "PR NewsWire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "In California, a new public service announcement (PSA) has been released on Feb. 19, 2025. The PSA focuses on the harmful effects of Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACEs) and toxic stress. Dr. Diana Ramos, the California Surgeon General, is leading the initiative to provide tools for healing and promoting resilience. The 30-second PSA aims to raise awareness about these issues and offer guidance to Californians. This initiative is crucial considering that ACEs affect approximately 50% of children in California, contributing to mental health challenges and other outcomes. Dr. Ramos stresses the importance of addressing these issues early on to prevent long-term consequences.",
